# Mintlify documentation (this repo)

## Discover upstream Mintlify docs first

Before changing navigation, components, or MDX patterns you are unsure about, discover what Mintlify documents:

1. **Documentation index**: fetch and skim [https://www.mintlify.com/docs/llms.txt](https://www.mintlify.com/docs/llms.txt) to see available pages, then open only the pages you need.
2. **Project navigation**: follow [docs.json](https://mintlify.com/docs.json) when editing `docs.json` and site structure.
3. **Mintlify MCP**: if the Mintlify MCP server is connected in Cursor, use it to search current Mintlify docs instead of guessing APIs or props.

## Submitting feedback (Mintlify.com docs only)

If official Mintlify documentation is wrong, outdated, or confusing **and you have something specific and actionable**, you may report it:

`POST https://www.mintlify.com/docs/feedback`

```json
{
  "path": "/guides/cursor",
  "feedback": "Description of the issue"
}
```

Use the real doc path you were reading. Do **not** submit vague or speculative feedback.

